<br>
First in order for this to work, all pet summonings post-50 must all summon at one level. I.e. the 51st pet everytime you cast it is always 40th level. 52nd pet is always 41st level. so and and so on. (These are just examples, not sure what level the actual 50+ pets are summoned at.) Basically like the Beastlord pets when they &quot;call&quot; them.<br>
<br>
Water Mastery: 1 AAXP - Increase the level of any water pet you cast by 1. (Post-50)<br>
<br>
Earth Mastery: (Same as Water, except replace Water with Earth)<br>
<br>
Fire Mastery: (Same as Water, except replace Water with Fire)<br>
<br>
Air Mastery: (Same as Water, except replace Water with Air.)<br>
<br>
Elemental Mastery: 1 AAXP - Increase the level of you Epic pet by 1. (You can't begian to increase this skill untill Water, Earth, Fire, and Air Mastery skills are at least 5.)<br>
<br>
<br>
The only limit to this is that you attain a pet that is higher than your level. This only increases the level of the pet, not its stats.<br>
<br>
<br>
Strenthen Elementals: 1 AAXP - Increase your pets strength by 5, 10, and 15 % (Level max 3) (Including the Epic)<br>
<br>
Agile Elementals: 1 AAXP - (Same as Strengthen Elemenals, except repace Strenth with Agility.) (Level max 3) <br>
<br>
Dexterious Elementals: 1 AAXP - (Same as Strenghten Elementals, except replace Strenth with Dex.) (Level max 3 )<br>
<br>
Resiliant Elementals: 1 AAXP - (Same as Strenthen Elementals, except repalce Strenth with Hit Points.) (Level max 3 )<br>
<br>
<br>
I feel this way we can strenthen out pets in the way we individually want, and Verant gets their oh-so precious time sinks that they love. Just an idea. <br>
